#WHY.DO.PEOPLE.LIKE.THIS.GAME?

First of all, WTF is with all the over 1000 hours players? Are people really that desperate?

Nexion Zombies is just an old school CS:GO game from the early 2000's that has been revamped in a few ways. Just take a quick look at the gameplay, it's from the "stone age." Yes, I know it is free, but the only work that has been put into the game has to do with microtransactions.


 If you truly want a good FPS zombie game, just pay for it. Here are a few popular zombie games that are very good.

1. Call of Duty World at War (referring to the old school mod king) -------- { $19.99}
    OK Multiplayer, OK Campaign, GREAT Nazi Zombie mods :)

2. Killing Floor 1 or 2 -------- { [1] $19.99, [2] $29.99}
    Fast paced, Unreal Engine gameplay, GREAT Multiplayer :)

3. Left For Dead 1 or 2 -------- { [1] $19.99, [2] $19.99}
    GOOD Multiplayer, GOOD Campaign, GREAT with friends :)

4. Nazi Zombie Army 1 or 2 -------- { [1] $14.99, [2] $14.99}
    Lots of shooting, GREAT with friends, Overall...good :)

Just as a heads up, many of these games are oftenly on sale....sooooo just keep an eye out.

Man, this thing is the worst ... i don't think i can call it a game, most likely a modification to a good old game thing:
-Confusing Menu for new players;
-CS with COD weapons and zombies. AWFUL;
-Nonsense missions and timeline;
-Kinda destroys the CS games' reputation ONLY because of the name;
-And too many other complaints. The only "good" thing is that you can play some original CS 1.6 maps without zombies. Other than that, i do not recommend this game to anyone... And, please, if you want good zombie games, check the other games, waaay better than this thing...
